# .easignore — governs the EAS Build upload archive.
#
# This monorepo is archived from the GIT ROOT (the 76 MB tarball that kept
# failing to upload included root-level docs/, PROGRESS.md, apps/web/ — so
# the ignore must take effect here). EAS uses this file INSTEAD of
# .gitignore for the upload, so the .gitignore patterns are replicated
# first (otherwise node_modules etc. would *balloon* the tarball), then
# build-irrelevant paths are excluded to shrink it.
#
# Added 2026-06-18 after the project tarball repeatedly dropped mid-upload
# on a degraded connection (38MB → 14MB → 3MB).

# ── git history (not needed in the build archive) ──
.git/

# ── replicated from .gitignore (must stay OUT of the upload) ──
node_modules/
.pnp
.pnp.js
.next/
dist/
build/
out/
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
.env*.local
*.pem
*.p12
*.key
credentials.json
token.json
apps/*/secrets/
*.tfvars
prisma/migrations/
.turbo/
.vercel
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.log
npm-debug.log*
*.tsbuildinfo
.expo/
apps/mobile/.expo/
apps/mobile/android/
apps/mobile/ios/
apps/mobile/dist/
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
expo-env.d.ts
# NOTE: apps/mobile/google-services.json is intentionally NOT excluded —
# EAS Build needs it in the archive (FCM config), and EAS filters
# .easignore patterns out of the archive even for tracked files.

# ── extra: shrink the upload (none of these are used by the Android build) ──
docs/
.github/
marketing_handoff/
.tmp/
/*.md
**/*.test.*
**/*.spec.*
**/__tests__/
**/__snapshots__/
**/*.snap

# apps/web is web-only (Vercel) and the mobile/shared packages don't depend
# on it. Exclude its source but KEEP package.json so the npm workspace +
# root lockfile stay consistent for the EAS `npm install` step (its
# postinstall runs `prisma generate` against prisma/schema.prisma, which
# is still uploaded).
apps/web/*
!apps/web/package.json
